Project Overview

This project is a Rainfall Prediction Web Application built using Flask, Python, and Machine Learning.
The app predicts whether it will rain or not based on weather parameters like temperature, humidity, pressure, and wind speed.

Model: Trained ML model (Rainfall.pkl) for predicting rain.

Scaler: Input features are scaled using scale.pkl.

Frontend: Simple HTML form (index.html) for user input.

Backend: Flask handles routing and prediction logic.

Features

User-friendly Web Interface

Input fields for MinTemp, MaxTemp, Humidity, Pressure, WindSpeed

Predict button to get results.

Accurate Rain Prediction

Uses a pre-trained ML model.

Returns chance of rain or no rain.

Error Handling

Displays error messages if the input is invalid.

Dynamic Prediction

Uses a data frame structure similar to training data to ensure prediction consistency.

Updated Features in Version 2

predict() function updated to handle only necessary fields:

Automatically calculates derived features like:

Average temperature (MinTemp+MaxTemp)/2

Duplicates of Humidity and Pressure for model compatibility

Sets default values for Rainfall and RainToday (0) for input.

Frontend input types updated to number for better validation.

