Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone <https://github.com/divyabhuma/Exploratory-Analysis-of-Rain-Fall-Data-in-India-for-Agriculture>
cd RainfallPrediction


Create and activate a virtual environment:

python -m venv venv
# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate
# Mac/Linux
source venv/bin/activate


Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


Requirements: Flask, pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, pickle-mixin

Usage

Run the Flask app:

python app.py


Open your browser and go to:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/


Enter weather parameters:

Min Temperature (Â°C)

Max Temperature (Â°C)

Humidity (%)

Pressure (hPa)

Wind Speed (km/h)

Click Predict.

If rain is predicted: Redirects to chance.html.

If no rain: Redirects to nochance.html.

Example Inputs for Rain Prediction
MinTemp	MaxTemp	Humidity	Pressure	WindSpeed
18	      24	   85	      1005	     15
20	      25	   90	      1002	     10
16	      22	   95	      1000      	20

